About Devoteam
At Devoteam, we believe that technology with strong human values can actively drive change for the better. Discover how Tech for People unlocks the future, creating a positive impact on the people and the world around us. We are a global leading player in Digital Transformation for leading organizations across EMEA, with a revenue of €652M. We believe in transforming technology to create value for our clients, partners and employees in a world where technology is developed for people. We are proud of the culture we have built together. We are proud of our people at the service of technology. We are proud of our diverse environment. Because we are #TechforPeople. Join our multidisciplinary team of Cloud experts, Designers, Business consultants, Security experts, Engineers, Developers and other extraordinary talents, spread across more than 18 EMEA countries. Become one of our +8.000 tech and business leaders on cloud, data and cyber security. Let’s fuse creativity with technology together and build innovative solutions that actively change things for the better.
  About the job
The purpose of the iOS Developer is to design, build, and maintain iOS applications.
Our ideal candidate for this role should have a background as iOS Developer and a good knowledge of iOS frameworks.
If this opportunity is for you, apply today!
   We will rely on you to:
- Be responsible for design, build, and maintain iOS applications;
- Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications;
- Collaborate with the team to define and design new features;
- Identify and correct bugs;
- Maintain the code and atomization of the application.
   What we're looking for:
- 2 years of experience in iOS development;
- Bachelor degree in Computer Science or similar;
- Experience with Swift, Objective-C and Cocoa Touch;
- Experience with iOS frameworks such as Core Data, Core Animation; 
- Good knowledge of push notifications, APIs, and cloud messaging;
- Fluency in English (spoken and written).
  Does this sound like you?
Come build with us, innovative solutions that actively change things for the better.
Apply today!

Viercode is a polish software company that connects best tech-driven engineers with best companies around the world in need of building or scaling their technology teams. We build high-performing teams of software engineers for the world’s leading brands.
 If you want to join our team, Viercode can guarantee you a professional development through work among professionals and experts, in a creative and friendly atmosphere. We also provide a lack of routine in performing daily duties.
 We value your time and your involvement. That’s why you have the possibility to work in flexible hours. Moreover, we assure reward adequate to engagement and performance.
 We are currently looking for a Data Scientist (Mid / Senior) to join Our Client project team in order to provide services in the full life-span of software production, such as: analysis and development of functional specifications, data analysis in source systems, defining business requirements, design, development, post-implementation maintenance of IT systems dedicated to support modern business processes, support in UAT end user tests.
 Remuneration depends on the level of experience in the position, as well as the outcome of the recruitment process.
 Mid 80-130 PLN / per hour + vat (B2B)
 Senior 130-170 PLN / per hour + vat (B2B)
 If you want to work in a powerful network surrounded by passionated experts - this is the job you have been looking for!
 Don't wait - send us your application to be a part of the Viercode team - most energizing community of engineers and get long-term projects for various industries!
   Interesting and ambitious projects - no routine or repeatability of activities
Flexible working hours
The possibility for taking part in international projects
Excellent work atmosphere, including team events, hackathons
Work atmosphere as close as possible to a startup within a large corporation
 Terms of cooperation
  As of now 100% remote work, hybrid model as target solution (office in Warsaw, PL)
Minimum Monthly Load – 80%
Expected Monthly Load – 100%
Communicative English is a must
Polish min. B1
   At least 2 years of professional experience in Data Science — working understanding of popular ML algorithms and ability to use them in business environment;
Advanced analytical skills including very good knowledge of SQL and Python, PySpark experience is a plus;
Experience with analysis of large data sets;
Problem solving skills, ownership — accountability for the quality and success of the outcome of your work;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills — essential in day-to-day cooperation with clients and the team;
 Role
 As a Data Scientist you will be tasked with developing analytical solutions using Python, PySpark, SQL Server and other data science libraries / technologies. You will manage parts of large projects and run smaller projects on your own. You will support clients in in-depth understanding of the key-drivers for their current and future success and solving the strategic and operational problems.
   building ML models based on business requirements and available data;
implementing data science functionalities in applications, supporting their integration with other services;
researching and introducing data science solutions in Spark (with Python);
participating in product development cycle activities: defect management, resolution process, Git repository maintenance, new feature design and implementation;
maintaining documentation (technical descriptions, user guides, business playbooks);
collaborating with international and diverse teams;
working in Agile software development model.
 It is expected that you will grow professional expertise through seeking knowledge, skills and hands-on experience in Data Science (through on-the-job learning, external events, conferences and training) as well as share your acquired knowledge with junior staff.

We are on a mission to make science open so everyone can live healthy lives on a healthy planet Who We Are Frontiers is the 3rd most-cited and 6th largest research publisher and we publish groundbreaking discoveries by the world's top experts. Scientists empower society and our mission is to accelerate scientific discovery by making science open. We place the researcher at the center of everything we do and enable the research community to develop the solutions we need to live healthy lives on a healthy planet. Join the publishing revolution. About The Role We are looking for a Knowledge Graph Engineer who can work on production-ready Artificial Intelligence (AI) to support our industry-leading AI publishing platform. Are you motivated by finding yourself surrounded by some of the industry's brightest minds working collaboratively on cutting edge data-driven products using the latest and greatest Machine Learning (ML) models and innovative algorithms? Are you thrilled by the prospect of seeing the output of your work utilized in a publishing platform that attracts 2 billion viewers and manages over 200k articles? Are you excited to research, design and develop innovative artificial intelligence products and their supporting pipelines? If that sounds great, then that's us: we are a cutting-edge product team working collaboratively as part of a larger AI department, supporting Frontier's industry leading AI products' portfolio. To empower scientists and radically improve how science is published, assessed, and disseminated to researchers, innovators and the public, we have built our own state-of-the-art AI Review Assistant (AIRA), as part of our AI products' portfolio. AIRA is backed by cutting-edge ML algorithms (covering areas such as computer vision, NLP, recommender systems); and featured in the media: https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/23/science/conflict-of-interest-ai.html https://spectrum.ieee.org/peer-review-of-scholarly-research-gets-an-ai-boost https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-021-03807-6 Requirements 
 Solid understanding of Semantic Web Technologies, such as RDF, SPARQL, SHACL, OWL and related tools, such as Graph DB, Neo4J, Protege, triplestore, Stardog and others;
 Experience in community detection algorithms such as Louvain or Leiden, feature embedding in large graphs and link prediction, and knowledge of SKOS, DublinCore, and Linked Data applications;
 Good understanding of Graph theory;
 5yrs+ experience in creating and maintaining knowledge graph data structures and in graph (data) analytics and inferencing;
 Experience using graphs in decision making;
 Knowledge of graph machine learning algorithms;
 Ability and experience in data integration;
 Experience in manipulating unstructured, semi structured and fully structured datasets;
 Willingness to share and adopt best work practices on a common codebase (Python packaging, version control, pull requests, testing, continuous integration);
 Familiarity with problem specification formulation and translation to functional/non-functional requirements ;
 Great communication, teamwork ethos, problem-solving skills and organizational skills. 
Benefits With more than 50 nationalities represented in our global team, you will work regularly with teammates in other countries, and with our community of researchers, editors, and authors from around the globe. Our mission to create solutions for healthy lives also extends to the working environment we provide for our employees. 100% remote working Employees now have the flexibility to choose where they want to work, with remote working available on a part- or full-time basis (not applicable to some Workplace/IT jobs due to nature of role requiring presence onsite, in the office). Learning and development All employees have access to LinkedIn Learning (and Pluralsight for our technology team), an annual personal learning budget, and dedicated L&D time. Wellbeing We offer free online yoga classes, an employee assistance plan, access to the Headspace app, and four wellbeing days on top of your annual leave allowance. Volunteering opportunities Employees can dedicate three days each year to volunteer for a personal cause or through our volunteering partner platform, Alaya. Frontiers actively embraces diversity and is a safe and welcoming workplace. Recruitment is free from discrimination – including based on race, national or ethnic origin, age, religion, disability, sex, gender identity or sexual orientation. With over 600 employees from more than 50 different nations, our diversity creates vibrant teams and constantly challenges us to appreciate multiple perspectives.

